    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/543.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Viceroy at Chengtu has arrested the ringleaders and his ya-men has been
                    attacked by a mob. The soldiers fired and killed some twenty rioters; some
                    soldiers were killed also. American ladies and children are reported to have
                    left Chengtu, with the British subjects. Troops are being concentrated on the
                    frontier of Szechwan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
